import {React, useState, useEffect} from 'react' import './Stats.css' function Stats() { const [github,setGithub] = useState([]) const [repos,setRepos] = useState([]) useEffect(() => { fetch('https://api.github.com/users/iampranavdhar') .then(response => response.json()) .then(result => setGithub(result)); fetch('https://api.github.com/users/iampranavdhar/repos') .then(response => response.json()) .then(repos => setRepos(repos)) },[]) const totalStars = () =>{ const each_repo_stars = repos.map(({stargazers_count}) => stargazers_count) //For getting the list of all the stars for each repo const total = each_repo_stars.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) //For finding sum of the elements in a list return total } return (
